6. limit() and skip()
Concept
    limit(n): Returns a stream containing only the first n elements.
    skip(n): Returns a stream after skipping the first n elements.
    
    Both are intermediate operations.
    
    Syntax
    // First n elements
    stream.limit(n);
    
    // Skip first n elements
    stream.skip(n);





1. Print the first 5 elements from a list of numbers.
Program
import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;

public class LimitExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        List<Integer> numbers = Arrays.asList(
                10,20,30,40,50,60,70,80);

        numbers.stream()
                .limit(5)
                .forEach(System.out::println);
    }
}
Output
10
20
30
40
50





